At 50k feet: SCIENCE!

  1. Make observations of the natural world.
  2. Generate theories/models.
  3. Evaluate the consistency between the model and the data.
  4. Gather more data, revise theories.
  5. Iterate…

Regression: the central statistical model

Regression is a method to express one variable of interest (the response) as a function of other variables (the predictors).

\[ Y = f(X_1, X_2, X_3 \ldots) \]

It is a probabilistic model.

\[P(Y | X_1, X_2, X_3 \ldots) \]

  • \(Y\): antral follical count / FSH / OV
  • \(X_1\): BPA concentration
  • \(X_2\): age
  • \(X_3\): race
  • \(X_4\): BMI

  • \(Y\): overdose death rate
  • \(X_1\): marijuana legalization
  • \(X_2\): opioid policy
  • \(X_3\): state unemployment rate

\(Y\): age
